==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A member of the species ''[[Homo neanderthalensis]]'', now extinct
# (perjorative) a primitive person

===Adjective===
'''neanderthal'''
# Of or pertaining to [[neanderthal]]s or the [[Neander Valley]] in [[Germany]].
#:The capacity of the ''neanderthal'' skull was 10% larger than that of modern humans.

===Etymology===
''Neander'' is named after theologian Joachim Neander (1650-1680); ''thal'' is the old German spelling of ''tal'' (valley).

